name: Sleeping Buddha statue Pupuan Tabanan
address: Jl. Pekutatan - Pupuan No.1, Pupuan, Kec. Pupuan, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82163, Indonesia
review 1: A nice spot to visit if you're already in the area.   Not many Buddhist places in Bali.  Not much to see....just the laying Buddha and a few other smaller shrines and gardens.  Donations are expected to enter.  I gave 20,000 which I think is the norm.
review 2: The monastery is very spectacular and amazing. I know it's quite far away. But totally very recommended if you visit to the north. No ticket entrance but you can give donation on the contrary. When I arrive at there I just feel peaceful and calm. Wear proper clothes when you visit there. There is two dogs also they are nice. Brown one Rocky and Juju.

review 5: Well worth a visit beautiful tranquil place
